What’s Entitlement Management?

Contract line items are products covered by a service contract. Learn how to perform basic actions on contract line items.

REQUIRED USER PERMISSIONS
To add contract line items to service contracts: Edit on service contracts, Create on contract line items, Read on products and price books.
To view contract line items: Read on contract line items, Read on products and price books.
To edit contract line items: Edit on contract line items, Read on products and price books.
To delete contract line items: Delete on contract line items, Read on products and price books.

Available in Salesforce Classic and Lightning Experience. Available in Professional, Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions with the Service Cloud.

Viewing Contract Line Items
Contract line items can be viewed by navigating to a service contract and clicking on the Contract Line Items related list.
The Contract Line Items related list shows all the line items associated with a service contract.

Adding Contract Line Items to a Service Contract
Contract line items can be added from the Contract Line Items related list on the service contract’s detail page.
Select one or more products, enter attributes and sales price for each product, and save changes.

Deleting Contract Line Items
Contract line items can be deleted from the contract line item’s detail page or the Contract Line Items related list on a service contract.
Deleting a contract line item moves it to the Recycle Bin. Any notes, attachments, or activities associated with the contract line item are also deleted.

Sharing Contract Line Items
Sharing for contract line items is inherited from service contract sharing.
Users with Read permission on service contracts inherit Read permission on contract line items.
